name: As per the requirements of AS3760:2003, CL:2.3.3.4, mS = Milliseconds for calibration test. >150mS for a 30ma RCD requires corrective action by electrician
Notes: for any calibration tests that exceed 150mS, record action
Installation of Cable & Wiring (Rough In) checklist
Template Name: Installation of Cable & Wiring (Rough In) checklist

name: Confirm that cable supports have been completed without interference from other services
Electrical services cables have been appropriately sized and selected to ensure that they will support electrical installation as documented:
Light circuits complete and light control
NBN conduit installed with draw wire
Locate & fix into position, bolt temporary board down with at least 2 fixings
Install submains cabling as appropriate eg: glands/tray/duct

Any cables not terminated prior to energisation must be removed from cubicle at origin and have ends covered in heat shrink. At destination cables must be covered in heat shrink and be contrained in a junction box
When ready to energise proceed in accordance with energisation procedure
Energise & record results on Vast RCD test sheet
Install A3 laminated sign on face of temp board with floor plan and where the board is fed from
Update Temporary Power Board register & save to project folder/design control/temp const.

Communication services conduits and cast in boxes have been installed in accordance with design and as per Electrical drawings.
Security services conduits and cast in boxes have been installed in accordance with design and as per Electrical drawings.
All Penetrations have been installed in accordance with design and as per Electrical drawings.
